Telekom Austria’s VIP Mobile Initiates HSPA+ Broadband in Serbia

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-02-11T12:14:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/telekom-austria-s-vip-mobile-initiates-hspa-broadband-in-serbia.html
VIP Mobile , a member of Telekom
Austria Group, upgraded its mobile broadband service in  Serbia ,
offering speeds of as much as 42 megabits per second by
introducing HSPA+ technology.  The new service initially covers Serbia’s six biggest
cities, or 31 percent of the country’s 7.3 million people, with
plans to expand the use of High Speed Packet Access by the end
of the year to other urban areas, the company said in a
statement posted on its website.    Telenor ASA  and of Telekom Srbija AD, the company’s two
rivals, offer speeds of as much as 3.6 mbits per second. VIP
Mobile said it has invested 618.8 million euros ($837 million)
in its Serbian operation so far, including 320 million euros for
the license in late 2006.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
